HEADWORD: Boatable
<hw>Boat"a*ble</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Such
as can be transported in a boat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Navigable for boats, or small river craft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>boatable</qex> waters of the Alleghany.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Morse.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boatage</ent>⟦br⟧
